John Schmitz
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer


Mr. Schmitz has served as Chairman and CEO of Select Energy Services since 2007. Mr. Schmitz founded Peak Oilfield Services, LLC in 2007, and the company was transformed into Select Energy Services under his leadership. Select Energy Services has experienced significant growth and transformation, both organically and through the strategic acquisitions of oilfield services and technologies.
A lifelong entrepreneur, Mr. Schmitz has founded and developed numerous successful businesses in the oil and gas industry including HEP Oil Company, Complete Production Services and Brammer Supply.

Founder and Chairman of HEP Oil Company, an exploration and production company that owns interest in over 1,500 producing wells
Founder of and served as the North Texas Division Manager for Complete Production Services.
Board member of Forum Energy Technologies, Inc.
President of B-29 Investments helping to provide financial capital to Select Energy Services
Founded Brammer Supply in 1983 and transformed company over 20 years into BSI, an integrated wellsite services provider
Past President of Cimmarron Gathering, LP, a midstream company focusing on natural gas and crude oil gathering.







Eric Mattson
Executive Vice President, Finance

View Experience







Eric Mattson
Executive Vice President, Finance


Responsible for the company’s finance organization, Mr. Mattson was appointed CFO in November 2008. Prior to the appointment, Mr. Mattson was an investor in Select Energy Services through his affiliation with Juniper Capital, an investment firm focused on oilfield service opportunities.
From 1993-1999, he served as Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Baker Hughes Inc., a leading oil service company. Having joined Baker International, Inc. in 1980, Mr. Mattson served in a number of capacities including Treasurer prior to the merger of Baker International, Inc. and Hughes Tool Co. in 1987 at which time he became Vice President and Treasurer of Baker Hughes, Inc.  (more…)
Education

Bachelor of Science in EconomicsThe Pennsylvania State University
Masters of Business AdministrationThe Pennsylvania State University







Gary Gillette
Senior Vice President & Chief Financial Officer 

View Experience







Gary Gillette
Senior Vice President & Chief Financial Officer 


Mr. Gillette joined Select Energy Services in June 2015 and serves as Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer. He brings over 30 years of industry experience to his position. He has a strong background in finance as well as managing business operations including supply chain management, human resources and information technology.
Mr. Gillette began his career with Ernst &Young (“EY”) before going on to serve in Finance and Operations roles with Thomson Tax & Accounting. Most recently, he spent eight years with Allied Oil and Gas Services, LLC, as the Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer.
CERTIFICATIONS

Certified Public Accountant | Texas State Board of Public Accountants
Chartered Global Management Accountant | American Institute of Certified Public Accountants

Education

Bachelor of Science in Business AdministrationConcord University
Master of Business AdministrationNew York Institute of Technology







Justin Briscoe
VP of Business Development

View Experience







Justin Briscoe
VP of Business Development


